    • Method Detail

      • onDiscoveryFinished

        void onDiscoveryFinished(@Nullable
                       java.lang.String apbJsonArray)
        This callback will happen when the native code has finished discovery. It is worth noting that this callback happens on a background thread and any UI calls in this callback should be run on the main thread. This is done to allow the callback a background thread to process the raw, json string on, before calling into the UI.
        Parameters:
        apbJsonArray - - Will be a json array of json objects sent from the apbs, or null on failure to find apbs
